# Trail Overlay — Project Context

## Purpose
Next.js app to overlay mountain bike trails on maps. Users upload GPX rides, trim segments into reusable trails, tag difficulty/direction, organize into networks. Includes a Chrome extension that injects trail data into Strava.

## Stack
- Next.js 16 (App Router), React 19, TypeScript 5
- Leaflet 1.9.4 (map), Tailwind CSS 4
- PostgreSQL (pg driver), JWT sessions (jose)
- Strava OAuth, Vercel deployment

## Directory Layout
```
app/
  page.tsx              # Server wrapper
  ClientPage.tsx        # Main state container (rides, trails, networks, editMode)
  layout.tsx
  api/
    auth/strava/        # OAuth init + callback (upserts user, sets cookie)
    auth/logout/
    upload/             # POST GPX/ZIP → parse → insert rides
    trails/             # GET (CORS-open), POST
    trails/[id]/        # PATCH, DELETE
    rides/              # GET (auth required)
    networks/           # GET (CORS-open), POST
    networks/[id]/      # PATCH, DELETE
    networks/[id]/map-overlay/     # GET, POST (Blob upload; auth)
    networks/[id]/digitization-tasks/  # GET, POST (auth)
    map-overlays/[id]/  # PATCH opacity (auth)
    map-overlays/[id]/alignment/  # PATCH two-point align (auth)
    digitization-tasks/[id]/  # PATCH, DELETE (auth)
    dev/dump/             # GET (secret header) — JSON snapshot for local seed
    health/
components/
  LeafletMap.tsx        # Interactive map; trail/ride/network rendering; trimming UI
  LeftDrawer.tsx        # Sidebar: upload, rides, trails (foldered), networks; TrailEditDrawer for draw/edit trail
  network/OfficialMapAndTasksPanel.tsx  # Per-network official map upload, 2-point align, digitization tasks
  trail/TrailEditDrawer.tsx  # Shared drawer form: pencil/eraser, undo/redo/clear, TrailFormFields, draw vs edit save
  AuthButton.tsx
lib/
  db.ts                 # pg pool; query() / queryOne()
  auth.ts               # getSessionUser() / getSessionUserId()
  session.ts            # JWT encrypt/decrypt; 30-day cookie
  gpx-utils.ts          # GPX + ZIP parsing (gpxparser, jszip)
  geo-utils.ts          # Haversine distance, elevation gain
  types.ts              # Shared interfaces
migrations/             # 001–012 SQL migrations (012: map_overlays, alignment points, digitization tasks)
browser-extension/      # Chrome extension (content.js, background.js, popup)
```

## Database Tables
| Table | Key Columns |
|-------|-------------|
| users | id, strava_athlete_id, name, profile_picture, access/refresh_token, token_expires_at |
| rides | id, user_id, name, distance, elevation, polyline (JSONB), point_count, timestamp |
| trails | id, name, difficulty, direction, polyline (JSONB), distance_km, elevation_gain_ft, notes, source, source_ride_id, uploaded_by_user_id |
| networks | id, name, polygon (JSONB) |
| network_trails | network_id, trail_id (junction) |
| map_overlays | id, network_id (unique), blob_url, image_width/height, transform (JSONB), opacity, optional source/title/printed_date |
| map_overlay_alignment_points | map_overlay_id, seq 1–2, img_x/y, lat/lon |
| network_digitization_tasks | network_id, kind, label, sort_order, optional completed_trail_id / completed_at |

## Key Types (lib/types.ts)
```ts
Ride          { id, name, distance, elevation, polyline: [lat,lon][], timestamp, pointCount }
Trail         { id, name, difficulty, direction, polyline, distanceKm, elevationGainFt, notes, source, sourceRideId, uploadedByEmail, createdAt }
Network       { id, name, polygon: [lat,lon][], trailIds, createdAt }
TrimSegment   { ride, startIndex, endIndex, polyline, distanceKm, elevationGainFt }
SessionUser   { id, name, profilePicture, stravaAthleteId }
EditMode      = 'add-trail' | 'edit-trail' | 'refine-trail' | 'add-network' | 'edit-network' | 'draw-trail' | null
difficulty    = 'easy' | 'intermediate' | 'hard' | 'not_set'
direction     = 'one-way' | 'out-and-back' | 'loop' | 'not_set'
```

## Env Vars
| Var | Notes |
|-----|-------|
| DATABASE_URL | Postgres connection string |
| STRAVA_CLIENT_ID | OAuth app ID |
| STRAVA_CLIENT_SECRET | Server-only |
| SESSION_SECRET | 32-byte hex for JWT |
| NEXT_PUBLIC_APP_URL | Base URL (browser-visible) |
| NODE_ENV | Controls cookie security |
| PROD_APP_URL | Optional — origin only, for `npm run db:pull-prod` |
| DEV_DUMP_SECRET | Shared with production; required header for `GET /api/dev/dump` |

## Architecture Notes
- Single Next.js/Vercel deployment (no separate API server)
- Leaflet loaded via `dynamic()` with SSR disabled
- CORS open on `/api/trails` and `/api/networks` for browser extension
- Trail trimming: client picks start/end indices on ride polyline → haversine math → save as trail
- GPX parsed server-side on upload; polylines stored as JSONB
- Browser extension injects into `strava.com/maps/create/*`, fetches trails from API

## Trail draw / edit UX (left drawer)
- **Draw trail** (`editMode === 'draw-trail'`): `TrailEditDrawer` variant `draw` in `LeftDrawer` — tools, history (draw undo/redo), network search, publish checkbox; map interaction via `trailEditTool` (`pencil` | `eraser`).
- **Edit existing trail** (`editMode === 'edit-trail'` + `selectedTrail`): same drawer variant `edit` — metadata + geometry in one save (`PATCH` trail with polyline + recomputed `distanceKm` from `ClientPage`). No separate “refine” step in the sidebar (`refine-trail` may still exist in `EditMode` union / mode registry for map descriptor compatibility; primary flow is unified under `edit-trail`).
- **Focused session**: while drawing or editing a selected trail, `LeftDrawer` hides the trails folder list (for draw), drafts, networks list, and rides list so the editor has room; picker hint shown when `edit-trail` with no selection. Drawer width target ~392px (`max-w-[392px] sm:w-[392px]`).
- **Map flags** (see `ClientPage`): trail pick on map when `edit-trail` without selection; geometry edit when `edit-trail` + `selectedTrail` + `refinedPolyline !== null`. `useEditMode` clears `refinedPolyline` / refine history when leaving `edit-trail`; seeds `refinedPolyline` from `selectedTrail.polyline` when trail id changes.
- **Geo helpers**: `lib/geo-edit.ts` (and updates to `lib/geo-utils.ts`) support interactive polyline editing used by the map.

## Official map + digitization tasks
- **Edit network** drawer includes `OfficialMapAndTasksPanel`: upload PNG/JPEG/WebP to Blob (`POST /api/networks/[id]/map-overlay` with `imageWidth` / `imageHeight` from client), **two-point align** (click feature on preview image → same feature on basemap → repeat), then `PATCH /api/map-overlays/[id]/alignment` stores points + `transform` (`lib/map-overlay-transform.ts` similarity fit).
- **Leaflet**: `ClientPage` holds `officialMapLayer`; `LeafletMap` draws the raster with a CSS `matrix()` from three projected corners (`imagePixelToLatLng`), `pointer-events: none`, z-index under interactive layers. Opacity slider persists via `PATCH /api/map-overlays/[id]`.
- **Tasks**: `network_digitization_tasks` rows; optional “complete when I save next drawn trail” links to `PATCH /api/digitization-tasks/[id]` after `POST /api/trails` from draw flow. **Draw trail** save also attaches trail to selected network (`PATCH /api/networks/[id]` trailIds) when `TrimFormState.networkId` is set.
- **DB**: run `npm run db:migrate` after pulling migration `012_map_overlays_and_digitization_tasks.sql`.
- **Prod → local:** `npm run db:pull-prod` calls `GET /api/dev/dump` on `PROD_APP_URL` with `x-dev-dump-secret: DEV_DUMP_SECRET`, then `scripts/seed-local.mjs`. Production must run the same migration so the dump includes overlay tables. Older dump JSON files without `mapOverlays` skip overlay/task sync.

## Branching / PR hygiene
- **`feature/trail-drawer-redesign`**: Web app drawer + trail edit work; based on `main`.
- **`extension/browser-extension-updates`**: Chrome extension–only commits; keep extension changes off the drawer feature branch so PRs stay reviewable.

## Agent / environment quirks
- Some environments wrap `git commit` with `commit --trailer …`, which **Git 2.28** rejects (`unknown option 'trailer'`). If that happens, create the commit with `git write-tree`, `git commit-tree <tree> -p <parent>` (message on stdin), then `git update-ref HEAD <new>`.

